You can use regex with Positive Lookbehind and Positive Lookahead to implement the extraction of the substring:

```java
public String getContent(String input, String start, String end) {
    // Compile a regex pattern for the given start substring and end substring
    Pattern pattern = Pattern.compile(&quot;(?&lt;=&quot; + start + &quot;).*?(?=&quot; + end + &quot;)&quot;);
    // Use the pattern to match input string
    Matcher matcher = pattern.matcher(input);
    if(matcher.find())
        // Matcher.group() returns the matched substring
        return matcher.group();
    return null;
}
```
